title: Shares of several REITs are trading lower amid market weakness as investors await today's Fed decision and statement on the economy. The Fed is expected to leave rates unchanged. UPDATE: Equities spiked following the Fed's decision to leave rates unchanged, with several stocks now up for the session.
Shares of several real estate companies are trading higher on continued upward momentum surrounding the economy reopening, which would increase consumer spending and economic activity.
Shares of several real estate companies are trading higher despite overall market weakness. Strength potentially related to the economy reopening, which could potentially increase mortgage demand.
6 Real Estate Stocks Moving In Thursday's Pre-Market Session

Shares of several real estate companies are trading higher as equities continue to gain on optimism over the economy reopening, which could potentially increase mortgage demand as well as a smaller-than-expected drop in nonfarm payrolls.
